title: The Bloody Forest - Battle for the Hurtge by Gerald Astor (epub)
description:
The Bloody Forest - Battle for the Hurtgen: September 1944-January 1945

By Gerald Astor
ebook, 416 pages
Published June 2nd 2010 by Presidio Press (first published July 11th 2000)
ISBN 0307755231 (ISBN13: 9780307755230)
Category:	Educational > Military History

Told largely through the words of men who were there, "The Bloody Forest" evokes one of the deadliest and most ill-conceived campaigns of World War II. "No one does oral history better than Gerald Astor".--Stephen E. Ambrose. 36 photos.
